payloadTypes.name: OAGIS JSON
payloadTypes.parsingScenarioData:
<scenario name="OAGIS JSON Parsing Scenario">

  <conditional>
    <test RoutingType="ContentBased">
      <!-- Payload parser for the OAGIS message -->
      <handler class="com.e2open.e2na.protocol.payload.oagis.JSONPayloadParser"
        propfile="OAGIS_PayloadJSONPathProps" />
    </test>
  </conditional>

  <!-- If received message is a ConfirmBOD, mark it FA not require -->
  <conditional>
    <test dataType="ConfirmBOD">
      <set sendFunctionalAck="false" />
      <handler class="com.e2open.e2na.protocol.payload.oagis.SetCorrelationJSON" />
    </test>
  </conditional>

  <!-- Determine whether ConfirmBOD is requested -->
  <conditional>
    <test payload.confirmation.code="Always">
      <set requiresFunctionalAck="true" />
    </test>
  </conditional>

</scenario>
payloadTypes.correlationScenarioData:
<scenario name="OAGIS JSON Correlation Scenario">

  <!-- Set the correlation id on the outbound for anything other than ConfirmBOD -->
  <handler class="com.e2open.e2na.protocol.payload.oagis.SetCorrelationJSON" />

</scenario>
payloadTypes.functionAckScenarioData:
<scenario name="OAGIS JSON FA Scenario">

  <!-- load the init process id ds on complete, for now -->
  <handler class="com.e2open.e2na.protocol.payload.util.LoadSplitOriginalMessage" />

  <!-- Handler to populate error properties depending on status of the datasource -->
  <handler class="com.e2open.e2na.protocol.payload.oagis.ConfirmBODErrorHandler" />

  <!-- Error properties used for transform, the props need to be defined for the 
    Informatica map to work -->
  <set BODID="${transactionId}" />

  <transform type="informatica" service="OAGIS_JSON_ConfirmBOD_FunctionalAcknowledgement" />
  <set dataType="ConfirmBOD" />
</scenario>

propertyDefinitions.name: TransportRetryLimit
propertyDefinitions.displayDescription: The number of times to retry due to not receiving a HTTP 200 response from trading partner web server.

propertyDefinitions.name: CustomAcknowledgmentRequired
propertyDefinitions.displayDescription: Defines if Custom Ack needs to be generated in response to any      Inbound call using this protocol. Takes only true/false value. Default is false. If false, then default XML ack is generated.      If true, then template must be defined using CustomAcknowledgmentTemplate.

propertyDefinitions.name: CustomAcknowledgmentTemplate
propertyDefinitions.displayDescription: Support file name added in the connection defining the template for custom acknowledgment generation.       Template should define actual ack format i.e. actual XML or JSON to be generated with any data source variable names from which       values to be replaced in the generated ack using the $ for variable names from the data source.

propertyDefinitions.name: SendAcknowledgment
propertyDefinitions.displayDescription: To disable the sending of Tech Ack to Partners who cannot consume it. Default is to send the Ack.

propertyDefinitions.name: OutboundMethodType
propertyDefinitions.displayDescription: Indicates the type of HTTP method to use when sending documents to partners.
